Hungary Ruling Party Sees Decline in Support, Nepszabadsag Says

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-04-20T06:55:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/hungary-ruling-party-sees-decline-in-support-nepszabadsag-says.html
Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban ’s Fidesz party lost support this month,  Nepszabadsag 
 reported , citing an Ipsos poll.  Fidesz was favored by 26 percent of those questioned, down
from 27 percent last month and the lowest percentage since
winning elections a year ago, the newspaper said.  Support for the Socialist Party, the biggest opposition
group, was unchanged at 12 percent and 48 percent were undecided
or said they didn’t plan to vote, Nepszbadsag said.  The newspaper didn’t give technical details of the poll.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  